{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "06", "m": "11", "Y": "2025"}, "time": {"H": "04", "M": "16", "S": "02"}}, "news": [{"title": "Land acquisition for New Noida project to begin soon", "para": "Land acquisition for the upcoming industrial township, New Noida (DNGIR), is commencing with a hybrid model involving direct purchase, mutual consent, and land pooling. Noida Authority is finalizing compensation plans for farmers across 80 villages in Gautam Budh Nagar and Bulandshahr districts, with rates influenced by proximity to the airport and existing land values.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/new-noida-industrial-township-land-acquisition-set-to-start-soon/125122543?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-166851/125122543.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "Delhi: Signature View residents to get rent from July 2023", "para": "Delhi Development Authority (DDA) will pay facilitation fees to Signature View Apartments residents displaced due to structural damage. The monthly compensation, starting at Rs 50,000 for HIG and Rs 38,000 for MIG flats, will increase by 10% annually until 2026. This decision follows a Delhi High Court order and aims to alleviate the financial burden on affected families.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/dda-approves-rent-compensation-for-signature-view-residents-from-july-2023/125122524?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-29334/125122524.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}, {"title": "Odisha REAT upholds homebuyers' rights in landmark ruling", "para": "The Odisha Real Estate Appellate Tribunal (OREAT) upheld a homebuyer's flat allotment, deeming its cancellation by a promoter arbitrary and illegal. The tribunal ruled the promoter violated the agreement and RERA Act by demanding balance payment before sale deed execution. OREAT ordered the promoter to accept the balance, execute the deed, and hand over possession, reinforcing buyer rights.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/rera/odisha-tribunal-defends-homebuyers-rights-in-pivotal-real-estate-case/125122476?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-107800/125122476.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "rera"}]}